MockHtmlUnitSessionTag
public class HtmlUnitSessionTag
extends SessionTag
implements HtmlUnitDelegate

A Session tag for the HtmlUnit plug-in. An example of its use might: 


 <testcase xmlns="jelly:jameleon">
     <htmlunit-session baseUrl="http://www.google.com" beginSession="true">
       <htmlunit-validate
           functionId="Check that title is Google."
           title="Google"/>
     </htmlunit-session>
 </testcase>

enableSslCertCheck

protected java.lang.Boolean enableSslCertCheck
Enable or disable validity checking of SSL certificates. If "false", invalid SSL certs will be accepted. If not set, the default is "true".

baseUrl

protected java.lang.String baseUrl
The url to use when starting the browser. This can be the entire URL including the path or not, but it must start with the protocol (e.g. http://some.domain.com)

beginAt

protected java.lang.String beginAt
If set, this would be the path after the protocol and/or domain. (e.g. /some/path/to/a/file.html)

enableSslCertCheckPort

protected java.lang.Integer enableSslCertCheckPort
The port to use to connect to https. Usually leaving it as the default should do.

store

public void store(java.lang.String fName,
                  int event)
           throws java.io.IOException
Description copied from class: SessionTag

Stores the current state of the object to a given File. The default implementation of this method does nothing. Override this method to implement plug-in specific behavior. Some examples might be:

  • Saving the HTML from an HTTP plug-in during a state change or error
  • Taking a screen shot for a GUI application during a state change event

A listener is already registered for each function tag. All that is required is implementing this method.

Specified by:
store in interface Storable
Overrides:
store in class SessionTag
Parameters:
fName - the name of the if the file to store the contents to.
event - The event that occured (error, state change ...).
Throws:
java.io.IOException - If the state of the object could not be stored in File f.
